***ABOUT TS FILES***

Other applications associated with file type TS:
Transport Stream (MPEG-2 Video Stream)
VOB files you find on a DVD are MPEG2-PS files. The PS format, however, is not adapted for streaming video through a network or by satellite. Another format called Transport Stream (TS) was designed for streaming MPEG videos through such channels. VideoLAN software can handle these streams. The identifying characters used for this association are - Hex: 47 40 , ASCII: G@ Related links: VideoLAN
